  <Name>Gladiator-Class Star Destroyer</Name>
  <Description>[H3][I]Gladiator [i]-Class Star Destroyer[h3]
Originally conceived by the legendary Walex Blissex as a Star Destroyer escort in the heavy battle lines of the Clone Wars, the [I]Gladiator I [i] was repurposed by the Galactic Empire as an independent, long-range patrol craft. The overpowered patrol vessel is able to project Imperial strength and pacify entire systems for up to two years without resupply. The [I]Gladiator [i] also has two battalions of stormtroopers, five AT-ST walkers, and the various shuttlecraft necessary to land them.
[P]
The 600-meter Star Destroyer packs incredible firepower, and it is equally comfortable performing system patrol, orbital bombardment, anti-ship, and escort missions. Its relatively low price point enables the Empire to send [I]Gladiators [i] throughout the Outer Rim, where they are unlikely to encounter anything more threatening than pirates in converted haulers or salvaged starfighters.</Description>
  <Source Page="78">Friends Like These</Source>
